\section{Prospects for elastic gauge boson production}

It is clear from $SU(2)\times U(1)_Y$ gauge invariance that the diphoton coupling of the resonance must be accompanied by a coupling to $ZZ$ , to $Z\gamma$ and potentially $W^+W^-$. From the effective couplings of Eq.~(\ref{eft}), there are two independent operators $f_B^{-1}\phi (B_{\mu\nu})^2$, $f_W^{-1}\phi(W_{\mu\nu})^2$. 
It is then convenient to express the event rates in the  $ZZ$, $Z\gamma$ and $W^+W^-$ final states as a function of the ratio $f_W/f_B\equiv r$. 
In particular, the ratios of the partial decay widths  $\Gamma_{VV'}/\Gamma_{\gamma\gamma}$ are given by \cite{Fichet:2015vvy}

and are shown in Fig.~\ref{fig:XS_VV}. The coupling to $(B_{\mu\nu})^2$ dominates for $r\rightarrow \pm\infty$, while the coupling to  $(W_{\mu\nu})^2$ dominates for $r\rightarrow 0$. 









